BP, International Consolidated Airlines Group, VW: European Equity Preview

-- B y   K a i t l y n   K i e r n a n
-- 
2011-09-27T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/bp-international-airlines-volkswagen-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx  Europe  600 Index gained 1.9 percent to 220.28.
The Stoxx 50 Index rose 2.1 percent to 2,094.08. The Euro Stoxx
50 Index, a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
advanced 2.8 percent to 2,083.35.  BP Plc (BP/)  : HRT Participacoes em Petroleo SA, a
Brazilian oil exploration company, offered to let TNK-BP operate
development wells while it focuses on exploration in  Brazil ’s
Amazon, said its chief executive officer. BP shares fell 0.1
percent to 384.70 pence.  International Consolidated Airlines Group SA (IAG LN): The
owner of British Airways Plc said the European Union’s emissions
trading scheme is a cost to airlines not a revenue stream and
the EC’s comment that the free allowances strengthen airlines’
financial situation is “outrageous.” The stock climbed 3.5
percent to 147.10 pence.  Volkswagen AG (VOW)  : Europe’s largest carmaker said it
received approval from the European Commission to increase its
holding in MAN SE (MAN GY). Volkswagen slumped 2.1 percent to 91
euros while engine maker MAN rose 0.4 percent to 59.03 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kaitlyn Kiernan in New York at 
